<TITLE> 8 get life term </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 22 (bdnews24.com)  A Netrakona court sentenced 7 men to life imprisonment in two cases on Thursday. A Magura court sentenced a woman to life in prison in a drug case. bdnews24.com's Netrokona correspondent reported that additional district sessions judge Md Akramul Haque Chowdhury gave life to six in a murder case. Another was given the same punishment in a case of kidnap and rape. All seven were also fined Tk 30,000 otherwise and sentenced to another year in jail if they were unable to pay the fine. The convicted are Bazlu, Wahab, Basu, Alaluddin, Akdil, Sattar and Yousuf Ali of Dashpara village of Netrakona Sadr Upazila. Among them, Basu died in 2004. According the case, the accused killed Shib Shankar of the same village on February 21, 2001. On next day Shib's brother Bishwajit Talukder filed a murder case with the Netrakona Model Police Station. A Netrakona women and child tribunal gave life-term to a man named Samrat Mia of Pabai village of Mohanganj Upazila. Samrat was also fined Tk 10,000 and given another year in prison in case of his inability to pay. According the case, Samrat kidnapped and then raped Shakiba Akther of the same village on March 14, 2004. The victim's brother Liton Mia filed a case with Mohanganj Police Station. Magura correspondent reported that the additional district sessions judge Md Nazir Ahmed gave life term and fined Tk 10,000 or another year in prison to a woman in a drug case. The convict is Mumtaz Begum Tuki, 35, daughter of Syed Akbar Ali of Sogia village of Maheshpur Upazila in Jhinaidah. Additional public prosecutor Md Moshur Rahman, lawyer for the state, told bdnews24.com that Magura Sadr Police Station's sub-inspector Abdul Baten had arrested Mumtaz for having 25 bottles of phensidyl from a restaurant at Magura bus terminal on April 14, 2007. A case was filed against her with the Magura Sadr Police Station on that day. bdnews24.
